	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-3041096502" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Bingo! Worked a treat, thanks Ryan. I downloaded the Mac archive from <a href="https://disq.us/url?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Fmozilla%2Fgeckodriver%2Freleases%3Am2-HoMplaVuKOHGuCAoN4jc6LUw&amp;cuid=1175718" rel="nofollow noopener">https://github.com/mozilla/gec...</a>, unzipped it, put the executable in my project root (though I guess it could have gone anywhere, and might more sensibly be kept somewhere like /usr/local/share or something.</p><p>As you described, I added the path to the executable to my path, and now I can run tests with Selenium.</p><p>Thanks again for your help!</p>
