	            	                <li class="dsq-comment dsq-clearfix" data-dsq-comment-id="2915170966" id="dsq-comment-2915170966">
	                    <div class="dsq-avatar dsq-tt">
	                        <a href="https://disqus.com/by/weaverryan/">
	                            	                                <img alt="" src="http://a.disquscdn.com/uploads/users/32/6480/avatar92.jpg?1482356913">
	                            	                        </a>
	                    </div>
	                    <div class="dsq-comment-body" id="dsq-comment-body-2915170966">
	                        <div class="dsq-comment-header">
	                            <span class="dsq-comment-date">2016-09-23</span>
	                            <span class="dsq-commenter-name">weaverryan</span>
	                        </div>

	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-2915170966" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2915170966" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Yea, I agree that it sounds like a session-saving issue. But since you say that you *can* see session files created, and that they are created on each request, then it makes me wonder if Varnish is stripping the cookies so that each request (to Symfony) looks like a fresh request (i.e. one that has no cookie). I would remove Varnish, at least to test, and see if that fixes the problem.</p><p>Cheers!</p>
	                            </div>
	                        </div>
	                    </div>
	                </li>
	            	                <li class="dsq-comment dsq-clearfix" data-dsq-comment-id="2910581020" id="dsq-comment-2910581020">
