	                                <p>hi, <br>   When i put this   " "require" : { "knpuniversity/guard-bundle": "0.1"    "   in my composer.jsno file and try to composer update  following error shows :</p><p>Your requirements could not be resolved to an installable set of packages.</p><p>  Problem 1</p><p>    - Installation request for knpuniversity/guard-bundle 0.1 -&gt; satisfiable by knpuniversity/guard-bundle[v0.1].</p><p>    - Conclusion: remove symfony/symfony v2.3.23</p><p>    - knpuniversity/guard-bundle v0.1 requires symfony/security-bundle ~2.6 -&gt; satisfiable by symfony/security-bundle[v2.6.0, v2.6.1, v2.6.10, v2.6.11, v2.6.12, v2.6.13, v2.6.2, v2.6.3, v2.6.4, v2.6.5, v2.6.6, v2.6.7, v2.6.8, v2.6.9, v2.7.0, v2.7.1, v2.7.10, v2.7.11, v2.7.12, v2.7.13, v2.7.14, v2.7.2, v2.7.3, v2.7.4, v2.7.5, v2.7.6, v2.7.7, v2.7.8, v2.7.9, v2.8.0, v2.8.1, v2.8.2, v2.8.3, v2.8.4, v2.8.5, v2.8.6, v2.8.7].</p><p>    - don't install symfony/security-bundle v2.6.0|don't install symfony/symfony v2.3.23</p><p>    - don't install symfony/security-bundle v2.6.1|don't install symfony/symfony v2.3.23</p>
